cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SOC

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with recommendation systems and their impact on web traffic. It could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it analyzes browsing logs of users on Amazon.com. Machine Learning (cs.LG) could also be a possible sub-category as the paper presents a method for estimating causal effects from observational data. Cybersecurity and Privacy (cs.CY) could be another possible sub-category as the paper deals with anonymized activity data. Finally, the paper could also belong to the Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC) sub-category as it discusses the impact of recommendation systems on web traffic and user behavior.
